race.comment: BRUNO CHOCOLATE (1) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by 1.5 lengths at this track in a handy 20.25 beating Elegant Flint. Can measure up again. CERISE (8) had been racing in honest fashion recording six placings in a row before finishing fifth (20.28) at this track latest. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings five times from seven attempts. Worth following up. CREEPER (2) turned in a plain effort last time when fifth at Murray Bridge over 350m behind Life's A Bounty (20.15) in a Grade 6. Was in the money the start prior. The form out of his last race has been franked. Worth another chance. ONCE A DIVA (5) was unplaced here last start but gets her chance to atone.
